25:59.225 --> 26:01.769
We don't belong here, let's go.

26:21.789 --> 26:22.873
- Yes please.

26:26.502 --> 26:30.673
Actually you can just leave
the bottle, thank you.

26:36.095 --> 26:39.074
- This brunch is
great, thanks Madison.

26:39.098 --> 26:40.098
- Sure.

26:51.485 --> 26:54.238
So, what did you
think of church?

26:55.531 --> 26:56.615
- Not like home.

26:58.743 --> 26:59.951
- Different.

26:59.952 --> 27:03.455
- Church is church Sam
how is it different?

27:03.456 --> 27:05.517
- Worship at the cross.

27:05.541 --> 27:06.935
- I don't understand.

27:06.959 --> 27:08.729
- Worship at the cross.

27:08.753 --> 27:11.064
Pastor James had a service.

27:11.088 --> 27:14.026
- We were just at a service
or almost at a service.

27:14.050 --> 27:16.634
- No a service for
me and my friends.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.303
- A service for you
and your friends?

27:18.304 --> 27:19.656
Oh a service for...

27:19.680 --> 27:22.475
- Yeah a service
for slow people.

27:24.977 --> 27:26.580
- Sam that's not what
I was going to say.

27:26.604 --> 27:28.123
- That's what you were thinking.

27:28.147 --> 27:29.427
That's what
everybody's thinking.

27:29.451 --> 27:30.584
- Sam.

27:30.608 --> 27:31.835
- It's like wearing your
insides on your outside.

27:31.859 --> 27:33.419
When people look at
me they don't see me

27:33.443 --> 27:35.563
they see my problems and they
don't look me in the eye

27:35.587 --> 27:39.051
because then they might have
to admit I'm an actual person.

27:39.075 --> 27:41.803
Sometimes I think what I've
got is catchy like the flu

27:41.827 --> 27:43.495
and if they get too close to me

27:43.496 --> 27:45.557
they might wake up
with what I've got.

27:45.581 --> 27:49.085
Then the short bus will
come for them too.

27:51.462 --> 27:52.463
I miss home.

27:53.381 --> 27:54.715
- I know you do.

27:56.217 --> 27:58.344
But this is our home now.

28:02.681 --> 28:05.184
Trying to make it work for us.

28:11.857 --> 28:13.234
- Everybody drinks.

28:15.361 --> 28:17.172
- It's just a little
bubbly with brunch.

28:17.196 --> 28:18.697
- It's your third glass.

28:20.032 --> 28:22.493
I'm a big girl Sam I can
take care of myself.

28:26.247 --> 28:27.248
- Yes I can.

28:37.591 --> 28:39.009
- Good morning Madison.

28:44.640 --> 28:46.142
- We're adjusting.

28:50.396 --> 28:52.666
Oh this is my brother Sam.

28:52.690 --> 28:55.168
Sam this is Joan my boss
at the art gallery.

28:55.192 --> 28:56.192
- Hi Sam.

28:59.405 --> 29:00.882
- I like your shoes.

29:00.906 --> 29:02.175
- Thanks.

29:02.199 --> 29:03.575
- You're welcome.

29:03.576 --> 29:05.387
- Well you passed inspection.

29:05.411 --> 29:06.411
- Good.

29:06.412 --> 29:08.598
That is good right?

29:08.622 --> 29:10.767
Madison I've been thinking.

29:10.791 --> 29:12.231
With everything going
on in your life

29:12.255 --> 29:16.884
I think maybe we should
cancel the gallery show.

29:18.299 --> 29:21.611
- Postpone it just until
things level out a little.

29:21.635 --> 29:23.471
- I'm almost finished.

29:24.638 --> 29:27.284
- Really there's no
need to postpone.

29:27.308 --> 29:29.267
- I just think you
need time to regroup

29:29.268 --> 29:32.330
and get used to
your new situation.

29:32.354 --> 29:34.166
- But I'm planning on
coming in tomorrow.

29:34.190 --> 29:36.275
You can see my progress.

29:37.818 --> 29:39.296
- Sam's great on his own.

29:39.320 --> 29:40.547
He does it all the time.

29:40.571 --> 29:42.507
There's plenty for him
to do at the apartment.

29:42.531 --> 29:44.092
Right Sam?

29:44.116 --> 29:44.926
- No.

29:44.950 --> 29:46.785
- He means no problem.

29:48.078 --> 29:50.498
- Well I'll hold off for now.

29:51.665 --> 29:54.436
Let's see what you have
and then I'll decide.

29:54.460 --> 29:55.628
- Thanks Joan.

29:56.545 --> 29:58.714
- But it can wait Madison.

30:01.759 --> 30:02.759
- No.

30:03.802 --> 30:04.802
It can't.

30:06.305 --> 30:08.806
- It was very nice
to meet you Sam.

30:08.807 --> 30:09.807
- Bye.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.040
- I'll be right back.

30:54.228 --> 30:55.520
What?

30:55.521 --> 30:59.042
- Some people wear their
problems on the outside

30:59.066 --> 31:02.403
for everyone to see,
some keep them hidden.

31:03.696 --> 31:04.881
And who would that be?

31:04.905 --> 31:05.840
- You.

31:05.864 --> 31:08.075
- Well Doctor Sam I'm fine.

31:09.702 --> 31:11.370
Just leave me alone.

31:15.749 --> 31:16.749
- I can't.

31:21.046 --> 31:23.381
- Yeah she likes yellow.

31:23.382 --> 31:26.217
- Just who are we picking
these for anyway?

31:26.218 --> 31:27.195
- Madison.

31:27.219 --> 31:30.198
- Your sister, how sweet of you.

31:30.222 --> 31:32.409
- Maybe she'll like me again.

31:32.433 --> 31:34.202
- Sammy Madison loves you.

31:34.226 --> 31:36.437
- But she doesn't like me.

31:37.896 --> 31:41.334
- She's never home anymore
unless you make her.

31:41.358 --> 31:45.279
- Being 11, a girl in
middle school isn't easy.

31:47.156 --> 31:51.409
- Neither is being nine,
a boy, and being stupid.

31:51.410 --> 31:53.388
- Sammy you are not stupid.

31:53.412 --> 31:55.164
- Madison says.

31:56.749 --> 31:58.852
- Yesterday on the phone.

31:58.876 --> 32:02.022
She was talking to
one of her friends.

32:02.046 --> 32:04.399
She said she couldn't
go to the movies

32:04.423 --> 32:08.653
because she has to baby
sit her stupid brother.

32:08.677 --> 32:11.740
- Sammy sometimes people say
things without thinking.

32:11.764 --> 32:13.742
She didn't mean that.

32:13.766 --> 32:16.518
Besides you watch
someday Madison

32:17.728 --> 32:19.771
is gonna see just
how smart you are.

32:19.772 --> 32:21.207
- But I'm not.

32:21.231 --> 32:22.940
- Yes you are very smart.

32:22.941 --> 32:26.111
- I know I'm smart
but I'm not a baby.

32:27.154 --> 32:29.615
- You will always be my baby.

32:32.284 --> 32:35.537
- So which one should
we pick next Sam?

32:43.462 --> 32:44.462
- Sam.

32:46.256 --> 32:47.633
It is Sam?

32:50.636 --> 32:52.405
- Yes, Sam.

32:52.429 --> 32:53.948
- Oh good.

32:53.972 --> 32:57.786
Thought I was gonna have to
address you by your shoe size.

32:57.810 --> 33:00.622
Are you just gonna stand
there or are you gonna help?

33:00.646 --> 33:02.457
- I don't know what to do.

33:02.481 --> 33:04.334
- Of course you don't.

33:04.358 --> 33:06.211
That's the trouble
with kids today.

33:06.235 --> 33:09.881
They don't how to do anything
but book their face and twit.

33:09.905 --> 33:11.990
Get over here, come here.

33:13.075 --> 33:14.075
Come on.

33:16.120 --> 33:17.538
Now put these on.

33:18.664 --> 33:20.666
They'll keep the
manure off your hands.

33:22.084 --> 33:24.002
- You know animal dung.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.003
Poop.

33:27.506 --> 33:29.693
Oh don't give me that look.

33:29.717 --> 33:31.361
It's perfectly natural.

33:31.385 --> 33:34.679
Look the plants need
nutrients in order to grow.

33:34.680 --> 33:37.325
And plants get nutrients
from what animals eat

33:37.349 --> 33:40.519
and that eventually
turns into manure.

33:42.104 --> 33:44.374
And without it plants don't grow

33:44.398 --> 33:46.734
and you my friend don't eat.

33:49.778 --> 33:52.257
Where did you think
produce comes from?

33:52.281 --> 33:53.949
- The grocery store.

33:54.867 --> 33:56.219
- The grocery store what a.

33:56.243 --> 33:57.679
What do they teach
you in school?

33:57.703 --> 33:58.912
- I worked there.

33:59.872 --> 34:01.766
- The grocery store back home.

34:01.790 --> 34:03.208
- Oh yeah, I see.

34:06.879 --> 34:09.547
Well now you know
where the groceries

34:09.547 --> 34:11.717
that you bagged came from.

34:14.678 --> 34:18.599
- Yeah and they also need
water so get to work.

34:34.406 --> 34:36.408
- It's good, thanks Roy.

34:37.326 --> 34:39.179
- It's well deserved.

34:39.203 --> 34:41.913
We had a very good
morning in the garden.

34:41.914 --> 34:45.518
- Sorry about cutting
the zucchini vine.

34:45.542 --> 34:47.896
- You had to bring
that up right?

34:47.920 --> 34:49.397
Don't worry about it.

34:49.420 --> 34:52.734
It could have been a weed
it's an honest mistake.

34:52.757 --> 34:54.592
- I make a lot of mistakes.

34:56.303 --> 34:59.824
The key is to learn from
them and then move on.

34:59.848 --> 35:01.517
- Everyone's so much

35:05.270 --> 35:06.270
smarter.

35:07.564 --> 35:09.942
- Oh Sam is that
what you believe?

35:11.485 --> 35:12.485
Oh no no.

35:15.322 --> 35:17.634
You like to watch
thunderstorms right?

35:17.658 --> 35:18.968
- I guess.

35:18.992 --> 35:21.346
- Now when a thunderstorm
is rolling in

35:21.370 --> 35:24.933
first you see a flash
of lightening.

35:24.957 --> 35:28.125
And then a few seconds later
you hear the boom right?

35:28.126 --> 35:29.604
- Right.

35:29.628 --> 35:32.982
- Well that's because light
moves faster than sound.

35:33.006 --> 35:36.133
You see it before you hear it.

35:36.134 --> 35:37.654
And the way I look
at it the same thing

35:37.678 --> 35:39.303
could be said about some people.

35:39.304 --> 35:42.807
I mean some people
may appear bright.

35:42.808 --> 35:45.537
Until they open
their mouths, boom.

35:45.561 --> 35:47.563
Then you know the truth.

35:48.814 --> 35:50.524
Your cone's dripping.

35:56.488 --> 35:57.990
- Come on pick up.

35:59.658 --> 36:00.658
Sam?

36:05.205 --> 36:07.392
Sam where are you?

36:07.416 --> 36:09.835
Just give me a call back now.

36:14.923 --> 36:16.508
- No and I said I would call.

36:17.801 --> 36:19.904
- No no I'm fine.

36:19.928 --> 36:22.407
He can take care of himself.

36:22.431 --> 36:24.683
I've got to get these done.

36:28.854 --> 36:32.125
What do you think of this one?

36:32.149 --> 36:33.150
No this way.

36:37.863 --> 36:39.531
- It's nice.

36:41.533 --> 36:43.303
It's not finished yet.

36:43.327 --> 36:45.537
- Frankly it's
missing something.

36:47.039 --> 36:48.516
What's it missing?

36:48.540 --> 36:51.269
- I think you not knowing
what's missing is the problem.

36:51.293 --> 36:53.062
- Joan I don't have
time for your riddles.

36:53.086 --> 36:55.064
- Madison ever
since I've met you

36:55.088 --> 36:56.547
what's impressed
me about your work

36:56.548 --> 36:59.319
is that when I look
at it I see you,

36:59.343 --> 37:01.470
your feelings, your heart.

37:03.347 --> 37:05.057
It's missing you.

37:07.100 --> 37:08.101
I'll get it.

37:16.902 --> 37:17.902
Feelings?

37:19.237 --> 37:20.489
Want to see me?

37:21.615 --> 37:24.701
You know want to know
what I'm thinking?

37:27.079 --> 37:29.057
I'll show you.

37:29.081 --> 37:31.124
You want to see my heart?

37:32.417 --> 37:33.752
There, finished.

37:36.254 --> 37:39.484
- Madison you have a visitor.

37:39.508 --> 37:42.028
- I can come back another time.

37:42.052 --> 37:44.054
- No it's okay, come in.

37:45.347 --> 37:47.182
- Call if you need me.

37:51.561 --> 37:54.106
- It's nice to see you again.

37:56.566 --> 37:59.879
- Oh yeah, I'm Pastor Jason
Bridges from church.

37:59.903 --> 38:00.903
- Oh right.

38:01.947 --> 38:05.449
Sorry I didn't recognize
you without the...

38:05.450 --> 38:07.178
- You mean without the uniform.

38:07.202 --> 38:09.806
- Something like that.

38:09.830 --> 38:10.807
Hi.

38:10.831 --> 38:11.831
- Hi.

38:13.792 --> 38:14.792
- Oh sorry.

38:24.761 --> 38:26.030
Let's have a seat.

38:26.054 --> 38:27.305
- Oh thank you.

38:32.853 --> 38:36.290
This has a dadaist
quality to it.

38:36.314 --> 38:37.594
You know a little
bit of futurism

38:37.618 --> 38:39.036
with the destruction there.

38:40.819 --> 38:42.029
- Oh I'm sorry.

38:43.864 --> 38:45.383
I just wanted to follow up on

38:45.407 --> 38:46.991
your visit to our
church on Sunday.

38:46.992 --> 38:47.992
- Oh right.

38:49.327 --> 38:51.207
Look I'm sorry that my
brother disrupted service

38:51.231 --> 38:53.516
but please know that
it won't happen again.

38:53.540 --> 38:56.185
- No, no actually I
want to apologize

38:56.209 --> 38:59.188
that we didn't make the service
easier for you and Sam.

38:59.212 --> 39:00.372
I didn't realize that he's...

39:01.824 --> 39:02.984
Is he a special needs person?

39:03.008 --> 39:04.008
- No, no.

39:05.177 --> 39:08.346
That he's a person
with special needs.

39:10.140 --> 39:11.682
Pastor James filled me in on

39:11.683 --> 39:13.851
all that's happened
to your family.

39:13.852 --> 39:16.688
I'm so sorry about your mother.

39:18.648 --> 39:22.819
- Look he, I, both of us just
want to be able to help.

39:24.780 --> 39:27.199
- That's nice but we're okay.

39:28.200 --> 39:29.785
Everything is good.

39:31.745 --> 39:32.745
- I see.

39:35.499 --> 39:39.353
I hope you'll consider coming
back to worship with us again.

39:39.377 --> 39:42.546
- I don't think
that's a good idea.

39:42.547 --> 39:44.548
At least not right now.

39:44.549 --> 39:47.135
- Well it's an open invitation.

39:53.308 --> 39:54.308
- Pastor.

39:55.727 --> 39:57.246
Don't read too much
into the evidence

39:57.270 --> 39:59.898
left by moments of frustration.

40:00.732 --> 40:02.210
- I won't.

40:02.234 --> 40:04.378
And I hope you won't
read too much

40:04.402 --> 40:08.072
into the failed attempt
of a congregation to well

40:08.073 --> 40:12.303
welcome someone the way Jesus
would have welcomed them.

40:12.327 --> 40:15.412
Well thanks for
your time Madison.

40:15.413 --> 40:16.998
Have a blessed day.

40:30.387 --> 40:32.096
- So here's a list of
everything they took.

40:32.097 --> 40:33.449
They took my laptop.

40:33.473 --> 40:35.159
They cleared out our coolers.

40:35.183 --> 40:36.786
They took all of our cash.

40:36.810 --> 40:38.412
- It's the same M.O. that we had

40:38.436 --> 40:40.206
with Don's hardware
store last week.

40:40.230 --> 40:42.250
- Fort Barber just isn't
what it used to be.

40:42.274 --> 40:44.276
- Brittany Wells,
Channel Seven News.

40:47.571 --> 40:49.364
- Looks like another
gang related burglary.

40:50.699 --> 40:52.617
- Yeah it's the fifth
one in the last month.

40:54.244 --> 40:56.013
- No but I got to tell you.

40:56.037 --> 40:57.317
The chief is getting a whole lot

40:57.341 --> 40:59.142
of anxious about this going on.

40:59.166 --> 41:00.958
- Yeah I bet.

41:00.959 --> 41:02.294
- Excuse me son.

41:03.461 --> 41:05.064
You need to be on this
side of the tape.

41:05.088 --> 41:06.463
- Sam come away from there.

41:06.464 --> 41:08.133
- Pro Wind sport shoe.

41:09.426 --> 41:10.706
- This shoe print
it's a Pro Wind

41:10.730 --> 41:12.440
sport shoe men's size
eight and a half.

41:13.638 --> 41:15.478
- And this one is a Dash
high top men's size 11

41:15.502 --> 41:17.952
with a slash or a cut
running across the

41:17.976 --> 41:21.146
sole from the big toe
down the center.

41:23.273 --> 41:24.792
Like those shoes.

41:24.816 --> 41:25.960
- Let's get out of here.

41:25.984 --> 41:26.878
- You two stop.

41:26.902 --> 41:27.879
Grady those are suspects.

41:27.903 --> 41:30.631
711 my partner's
in foot pursuit.

41:30.655 --> 41:31.989
What's that cut through?

41:31.990 --> 41:33.992
Yeah I'm running over there now.

41:39.623 --> 41:41.851
- Excuse me, Brittany Wells
with channel seven news.

41:41.875 --> 41:43.895
May I ask you a few questions?

41:43.919 --> 41:45.313
- I'm Sam.

41:45.337 --> 41:47.023
Nice shoes.

41:47.047 --> 41:48.524
- Thanks.

41:48.548 --> 41:51.652
So Sam how do you feel about
solving the crime spree?

41:51.676 --> 41:52.820
- I'm hungry.

41:52.844 --> 41:54.596
- There's your scoop.

41:59.017 --> 42:00.018
Alright good.

42:01.311 --> 42:05.499
Hamburger number two for
our growing young man.

42:05.523 --> 42:07.501
Here you go Sam.

42:07.525 --> 42:09.325
You know it's been a long
time since I've seen

42:09.349 --> 42:12.048
this apartment look
this clean and neat.

42:12.072 --> 42:14.698
- I doubt Madison will
notice either way.

42:14.699 --> 42:17.011
- Yeah probably not.

42:17.035 --> 42:18.346
So how was that first burger?

42:18.370 --> 42:19.639
Was it to your liking?

42:19.663 --> 42:21.098
- Perfect.

42:21.122 --> 42:24.668
- Good 'cause I made the
second one exactly the same.

42:26.086 --> 42:29.881
So tell me Sam what is it
with your interest in shoes?

42:32.592 --> 42:34.094
- Shoes don't lie.

42:36.805 --> 42:40.451
- Boots, flip flops,
deck shoes, loafers,

42:40.475 --> 42:43.955
pumps, sandals,
sneakers, wing tips,

42:43.979 --> 42:47.166
steel toe, no toe, polished
or unpolished shoes,

42:47.190 --> 42:49.566
loose laces, no laces, Velcro,

42:49.567 --> 42:51.236
they all tell me what
a person's like.

42:53.446 --> 42:55.758
- I can tell where
a person's been.

42:55.782 --> 42:57.908
Sometimes where they're going,

42:57.909 --> 43:01.788
how old they are and what
they do for a living.

43:03.415 --> 43:06.560
- What do my shoes
tell you about me?

43:06.584 --> 43:07.752
- You step in poop a lot.

43:09.504 --> 43:12.257
- Well that's an understatement.

43:13.925 --> 43:16.862
- Job, oh no I'm retired.

43:16.886 --> 43:18.847
I did work for the
federal government.

43:19.806 --> 43:21.641
- Absolutely not.

43:23.893 --> 43:28.124
- No no nothing like,
well there was that...

43:28.148 --> 43:32.110
No no I worked for the United
States Postal Service.

43:33.236 --> 43:34.964
- The Postal Service.

43:34.988 --> 43:36.632
- You were a mail carrier.

43:36.656 --> 43:39.576
- Well not just a
mail carrier Sam.

43:40.785 --> 43:43.097
I have you know I
was the Postmaster

43:43.121 --> 43:46.892
right here in Fort
Barber for 32 years.

43:46.916 --> 43:48.668
- Cool I guess.

43:50.253 --> 43:54.299
Your right, postal service
is not what it used to be.

43:55.342 --> 43:57.403
You're too young to know but

43:57.427 --> 43:59.803
the postal service
used to be glamorous.

43:59.804 --> 44:01.240
- You're kidding.

44:01.264 --> 44:02.474
- No no really.

44:03.808 --> 44:06.579
Used to be in the old
days people would wait

44:06.603 --> 44:10.147
for the mail carrier to
come to their house.

44:10.148 --> 44:12.335
I mean when they saw the
mail carrier on their street

44:12.359 --> 44:16.488
their heart would race,
their pulse would speed up.

44:21.076 --> 44:22.276
You never knew what they might

44:22.300 --> 44:24.472
be delivering to your mailbox.

44:24.496 --> 44:27.831
I mean it could be a
hand written letter

44:27.832 --> 44:31.812
from a friend or relative
you haven't seen for years.

44:31.836 --> 44:34.839
You know people used
to write letters.

44:36.800 --> 44:39.153
Maybe it's a postcard
from someone

44:39.177 --> 44:42.263
visiting an exotic
or far away place.

44:43.681 --> 44:47.703
Maybe it's a Christmas catalog
from your favorite store.

44:47.727 --> 44:51.898
Or even a note from someone
expressing their undying love.

44:55.276 --> 44:58.839
Now nobody mails anything
of importance anymore.

44:58.863 --> 45:02.200
Just bills, and junk
mail and more bills.

45:03.660 --> 45:08.265
People are too busy texting,
and facing, and twitting.

45:08.289 --> 45:09.934
Say I'll tell you something.

45:09.958 --> 45:13.145
