01:04:59.896 --> 01:05:02.232
a dent free trash can since.

01:05:07.112 --> 01:05:08.947
Oh no I never married.

01:05:11.867 --> 01:05:12.867
- Well.

01:05:14.244 --> 01:05:16.139
It wasn't 'cause
I didn't want to

01:05:16.163 --> 01:05:19.225
or didn't have the opportunity.

01:05:19.249 --> 01:05:22.084
I mean back in the
day I was one of.

01:05:22.085 --> 01:05:25.255
Fort Barber's most
eligible bachelors.

01:05:26.381 --> 01:05:28.192
Bobby Collins and me.

01:05:28.216 --> 01:05:31.821
See Bobby had been the quarterback
of the football team.

01:05:31.845 --> 01:05:36.016
But what I lacked in brawn
I made up for in brains.

01:05:38.268 --> 01:05:42.040
I remember there was this one
time I tricked him out...

01:05:42.064 --> 01:05:46.234
Anyway I just decided it would
be better if I didn't marry.

01:05:52.449 --> 01:05:55.243
- I didn't want
to have children.

01:05:56.828 --> 01:06:00.289
I was afraid that
if I had a child

01:06:00.290 --> 01:06:02.626
he or she would be like Tom.

01:06:03.835 --> 01:06:05.294
- Like me.

01:06:05.295 --> 01:06:06.295
- Yeah.

01:06:08.548 --> 01:06:10.133
- You're smart Roy.

01:06:11.176 --> 01:06:13.845
- Oh no Sam, Sam I am not smart.

01:06:14.805 --> 01:06:15.805
No,

01:06:16.807 --> 01:06:18.016
far from smart.

01:06:18.975 --> 01:06:20.435
And you know why?

01:06:21.770 --> 01:06:24.480
Sam I would have been
blessed beyond belief

01:06:24.481 --> 01:06:27.317
to have had a child
just like you.

01:06:29.903 --> 01:06:30.987
- Thanks Roy.

01:06:32.948 --> 01:06:35.033
- No thank you my friend.

01:06:36.660 --> 01:06:37.660
Well.

01:06:38.745 --> 01:06:40.765
Why don't we head home?

01:06:40.789 --> 01:06:45.019
- No I said I would be here until 8:00 p.m.
I should stay.

01:06:45.043 --> 01:06:47.188
- Oh okay I'll wait with you.

01:06:47.212 --> 01:06:49.172
- No no I got this Roy.

01:06:50.632 --> 01:06:51.632
- Okay.

01:06:52.634 --> 01:06:53.634
Sure.

01:06:55.345 --> 01:06:56.614
Goodnight Sam.

01:06:56.638 --> 01:06:58.366
- Goodnight.

01:06:58.390 --> 01:06:59.390
Roy?

01:07:00.142 --> 01:07:01.327
- Yeah Sam.

01:07:01.351 --> 01:07:05.021
- Thanks for the hot dog
and for Tom's shoes.

01:07:07.733 --> 01:07:08.733
- Bye Tom.

01:08:26.185 --> 01:08:27.270
- Looks like we got a hero.

01:08:28.354 --> 01:08:30.374
We got us a real hero?

01:08:30.398 --> 01:08:31.398
Lucky us.

01:08:32.359 --> 01:08:33.752
Good thing you guys
got out in time

01:08:33.777 --> 01:08:35.796
so we could congratulate him.

01:08:35.821 --> 01:08:38.758
- What do you got
in the box hero?

01:08:38.782 --> 01:08:40.259
- Shoes.

01:08:40.283 --> 01:08:43.495
I've been collecting
them for the poor.

01:08:44.787 --> 01:08:47.225
Do you want to make
a contribution?

01:08:47.249 --> 01:08:49.584
- Yeah we got something for you.

01:08:51.877 --> 01:08:53.127
- Yes.

01:08:53.129 --> 01:08:55.191
- Yeah well Sam you
know the way you.

01:08:55.215 --> 01:08:58.300
ID'd these guys from
their shoe prints wow.

01:08:58.301 --> 01:09:01.636
We were thinking that you
should have their shoes.

01:09:01.638 --> 01:09:02.805
- You shouldn't steal.

01:09:02.805 --> 01:09:05.934
- I know I know, it's
societies fault.

01:09:06.977 --> 01:09:09.478
Wasn't I just saying that?

01:09:09.479 --> 01:09:10.706
- All the time.

01:09:10.729 --> 01:09:13.960
- I mean kids what are
you gonna do right?

01:09:13.984 --> 01:09:16.587
I mean they're constantly
doing things they shouldn't.

01:09:16.611 --> 01:09:20.782
Like you for instance walking
around here alone after dark.

01:09:22.325 --> 01:09:24.365
- Or putting up signs all
over town telling everyone

01:09:24.389 --> 01:09:27.662
that you're gonna be in
that park collecting shoes.

01:09:27.663 --> 01:09:29.832
It's a shame.

01:09:29.832 --> 01:09:30.725
- I have to go.

01:09:30.750 --> 01:09:31.750
- Yeah.

01:09:32.419 --> 01:09:33.419
You do.

01:09:34.671 --> 01:09:38.359
Sam that trick with the shoes
though that was impressive.

01:09:38.383 --> 01:09:39.652
We want to help you.

01:09:39.676 --> 01:09:42.279
We want to help you
identify us later so

01:09:42.304 --> 01:09:44.448
we're gonna leave you a
few more shoe prints

01:09:44.471 --> 01:09:45.890
all over your body.

01:09:53.564 --> 01:09:55.001
Hit him go on.

01:09:55.025 --> 01:09:56.401
Get him, get him.

01:09:57.986 --> 01:09:59.529
Alright get him up.

01:10:22.427 --> 01:10:23.427
Lets go.

01:10:32.729 --> 01:10:33.789
Sammy?

01:10:33.813 --> 01:10:34.813
- I'm here.

01:10:36.399 --> 01:10:38.360
Come here.

01:10:58.421 --> 01:10:59.714
Sam.

01:11:01.383 --> 01:11:02.591
Sam.

01:11:02.592 --> 01:11:04.236
Sam can you hear me?

01:11:04.260 --> 01:11:06.364
- Let's proceed to room four.

01:11:06.388 --> 01:11:08.931
We'll be with you in one moment.

01:11:08.932 --> 01:11:10.252
- I'm sorry you
need to wait here.

01:11:10.276 --> 01:11:11.535
- I want to go with him.

01:11:11.559 --> 01:11:13.603
- We'll come get you as
soon as possible I promise.

01:11:38.461 --> 01:11:39.796
- Sam I'm sorry.

01:11:41.673 --> 01:11:42.673
So sorry.

01:11:54.978 --> 01:11:56.479
How is he?

01:11:57.647 --> 01:12:00.209
- Doctor says he'll make it.

01:12:00.233 --> 01:12:01.984
Couple of bruised ribs.

01:12:01.985 --> 01:12:04.422
Knee is pretty messed up.

01:12:04.446 --> 01:12:05.947
Slight concussion.

01:12:07.866 --> 01:12:10.636
They don't think there's
any internal bleeding but

01:12:10.660 --> 01:12:14.039
he'll be here just a few
days just to be sure.

01:12:19.377 --> 01:12:23.548
- When we were kids Sam
needed a lot of attention.

01:12:30.472 --> 01:12:32.474
- Our mom loved us both.

01:12:33.600 --> 01:12:36.871
She did the best she
could under some

01:12:36.895 --> 01:12:39.355
really difficult circumstances.

01:12:41.357 --> 01:12:42.776
- But I had to...

01:12:46.905 --> 01:12:48.197
Go with the flow?

01:12:48.198 --> 01:12:49.908
Step aside?

01:12:51.701 --> 01:12:53.368
- You could say that.

01:12:53.369 --> 01:12:54.496
- I rebelled.

01:12:55.413 --> 01:12:56.807
- Oh I see.

01:12:56.831 --> 01:13:00.042
- Not in the way that you think.

01:13:00.043 --> 01:13:01.877
I didn't do anything bad.

01:13:01.878 --> 01:13:05.215
In fact I tried to be
good, really good.

01:13:09.886 --> 01:13:12.055
- Everything, you name it.

01:13:12.931 --> 01:13:15.433
My grades, art, sports, dance,

01:13:19.270 --> 01:13:21.523
the student government,
ag club, drama.

01:13:24.567 --> 01:13:26.903
- Okay maybe not everything.

01:13:32.826 --> 01:13:35.679
Not that it seemed
to matter much.

01:13:35.703 --> 01:13:38.641
The grades, the
first place medals,

01:13:38.665 --> 01:13:42.251
the applause, scholarships,
whatever it was.

01:13:42.252 --> 01:13:46.422
Oh that's nice Madison but did
you see what Sam did today?

01:13:47.632 --> 01:13:49.425
Where Sam went today?

01:13:50.593 --> 01:13:52.863
Oh Madison listen
to Sam tell you

01:13:52.887 --> 01:13:56.099
the story about the
shoes he saw today.

01:13:57.267 --> 01:13:58.393
I hate shoes.

01:13:59.561 --> 01:14:02.540
One year I went barefoot
for an entire summer

01:14:02.564 --> 01:14:06.734
just for the hope that Sam
wouldn't be able to recognize me.

01:14:08.153 --> 01:14:12.591
- But eventually you had
to put your shoes back on.

01:14:12.615 --> 01:14:13.615
- Yeah.

01:14:14.617 --> 01:14:17.263
Made it easier to run though.

01:14:17.287 --> 01:14:19.348
- And enter Fort Barber.

01:14:19.372 --> 01:14:20.808
- And freedom.

01:14:20.832 --> 01:14:22.893
Finally I had control.

01:14:22.917 --> 01:14:27.005
I made the choices, the
decisions right or wrong.

01:14:27.881 --> 01:14:28.965
I had a life.

01:14:33.052 --> 01:14:35.805
'Til one day I
answered the phone

01:14:36.973 --> 01:14:39.474
and was sentenced
to being my mom.

01:14:39.475 --> 01:14:40.953
- Without the hope of parole.

01:14:40.977 --> 01:14:45.148
- I was gonna have to be her
for the rest of my life.

01:14:56.826 --> 01:15:01.473
On my way up here I caught
myself thinking that

01:15:01.497 --> 01:15:04.584
maybe it would be
better if Sam died.

01:15:06.544 --> 01:15:10.340
After all he'd be better
off in Heaven right?

01:15:11.966 --> 01:15:14.469
- Well we all will be someday.

01:15:16.179 --> 01:15:17.179
- Someday.

01:15:19.849 --> 01:15:21.017
But not today.

01:15:23.228 --> 01:15:27.856
When I saw him I realized
how foolish I had been

01:15:27.857 --> 01:15:31.611
to think that Sam was
God's curse on my life.

01:15:34.030 --> 01:15:37.885
Sam taught me that
it's not all about me.

01:15:37.909 --> 01:15:40.161
- Well now that is freedom.

01:15:43.081 --> 01:15:46.918
- Actually Sam has been
a blessing in my life.

01:15:49.754 --> 01:15:52.382
- Yeah yeah I have to admit it.

01:15:53.549 --> 01:15:56.385
I've been feeling
blessed myself.

01:15:56.386 --> 01:16:00.241
And not just because
Sam is in my life.

01:16:00.265 --> 01:16:03.101
But because you are
there as well.

01:16:06.498 --> 01:16:07.498
- Yeah right.

01:16:07.522 --> 01:16:08.523
- It's true.

01:16:09.399 --> 01:16:10.793
Well except for the loss of

01:16:10.817 --> 01:16:13.235
the occasional
garbage can or two.

01:16:13.236 --> 01:16:14.463
Or three.

01:16:14.487 --> 01:16:17.490
- Okay fine but I'm
very serious Madison.

01:16:19.242 --> 01:16:20.742
You have a brought a breath

01:16:20.743 --> 01:16:23.538
of fresh air into
that old house.

01:16:24.747 --> 01:16:28.042
And it is one that I
would greatly miss.

01:16:30.242 --> 01:16:31.522
- This seems like a good time to

01:16:31.546 --> 01:16:34.256
ask for an extension
on my lease.

01:16:34.257 --> 01:16:35.591
- Oh it could be.

01:16:37.969 --> 01:16:39.637
- Let's not get carried away.

01:16:40.805 --> 01:16:41.805
Yeah?

01:16:43.016 --> 01:16:44.017
- Excuse me.

01:16:46.602 --> 01:16:49.707
I'm sorry sir but
visitors aren't allowed.

01:16:49.731 --> 01:16:50.624
- Oh okay.

01:16:50.648 --> 01:16:52.650
- It's okay he's family.

01:16:54.277 --> 01:16:55.653
- Very good then.

01:17:00.450 --> 01:17:04.287
All nurses to the
nurses station.

01:17:08.291 --> 01:17:09.417
- Thanks Roy.

01:17:10.585 --> 01:17:13.439
- For what I didn't do anything.

01:17:13.463 --> 01:17:14.630
- You're here.

01:17:31.898 --> 01:17:35.252
- Maybe today wasn't
so bad after all.

01:17:35.276 --> 01:17:36.611
- Maybe not Sam.

01:17:39.614 --> 01:17:42.301
- Long enough to hear
you wished I was dead.

01:17:42.325 --> 01:17:44.136
- That's not what I said.

01:17:44.160 --> 01:17:45.160
- I know.

01:17:46.829 --> 01:17:49.831
Besides there might
have been a few times

01:17:49.832 --> 01:17:53.002
I wished the same
thing about you too.

01:18:03.554 --> 01:18:05.640
- It's right here Sam.

01:18:19.237 --> 01:18:23.365
- Scripture says love your
God with your whole heart,

01:18:23.366 --> 01:18:28.180
soul, and mind and to love
your neighbor as yourself.

01:18:28.204 --> 01:18:30.933
Now it would be very
easy to go through life

01:18:30.957 --> 01:18:33.602
if it was all about
our outward actions.

01:18:33.626 --> 01:18:36.730
But it's not just about
our actions only.

01:18:36.754 --> 01:18:39.650
It's about loving your neighbor

01:18:39.674 --> 01:18:42.027
and taking care of
their needs as much

01:18:42.051 --> 01:18:44.470
as you take care of your own.

01:18:45.847 --> 01:18:47.223
Roy what's wrong?

01:18:48.599 --> 01:18:51.954
- No no I'm sorry to disrupt
the service everybody.

01:18:51.978 --> 01:18:53.747
- That's quite alright.

01:18:53.771 --> 01:18:56.041
- No on second thought
you know I think

01:18:56.065 --> 01:18:57.960
we've all kind of gotten used to

01:18:57.984 --> 01:19:00.129
having our services
disrupted especially over

01:19:00.153 --> 01:19:04.716
the last couple of weeks by
a young fella named Sam.

01:19:04.740 --> 01:19:07.160
Let's carry on the tradition.

01:19:08.369 --> 01:19:10.745
I'm late because I
was visiting Sam.

01:19:10.746 --> 01:19:12.748
He's in the hospital.

01:19:14.750 --> 01:19:18.921
- Got the snot beaten out of
him by some kids in an alley.

01:19:20.256 --> 01:19:23.193
He was in the park collecting
shoes for the needy.

01:19:23.217 --> 01:19:27.239
Remember he told us
about that last week?

01:19:27.263 --> 01:19:29.867
He didn't get a lot of
shoes but he did get

01:19:29.891 --> 01:19:32.767
a lot more than
he bargained for.

01:19:32.768 --> 01:19:34.413
Hey look I'm not telling you any

01:19:34.437 --> 01:19:37.606
of this to make you feel guilty.

01:19:37.607 --> 01:19:40.586
I mean we all know
that God has done

01:19:40.610 --> 01:19:42.713
and is doing more
for us than we ever

01:19:42.737 --> 01:19:45.948
do for him or for any
of our neighbors.

01:19:47.116 --> 01:19:48.677
It's just that I
know that I for one

01:19:48.701 --> 01:19:50.262
have fallen into the
trap of thinking

01:19:50.286 --> 01:19:54.457
that if I sit in a pew in
church every week I'm good.

01:19:56.125 --> 01:19:59.587
And I realize that
coming to church alone

01:20:01.797 --> 01:20:03.817
makes me a Christian
just about as much as

01:20:03.841 --> 01:20:07.302
standing in the garage
makes me a car.

01:20:07.303 --> 01:20:11.325
Yeah Sam is a person with
special needs that's true.

01:20:11.349 --> 01:20:14.328
And that might make
us uncomfortable.

01:20:14.352 --> 01:20:16.330
But I'll tell you I've
lived in this town

01:20:16.354 --> 01:20:17.794
and I've been a
member of this church

01:20:17.818 --> 01:20:21.168
for a long long time
and I can't think of

01:20:21.192 --> 01:20:25.714
a single person I've met who
didn't have a special need.

01:20:25.738 --> 01:20:26.738
It's just

01:20:28.658 --> 01:20:30.719
like a wise young man
once told me some of us

01:20:30.743 --> 01:20:35.682
have our special needs on the
outside for everybody to see.

01:20:35.706 --> 01:20:38.668
Some of us bury them
deep in the inside.

01:20:39.919 --> 01:20:43.273
I'm sorry I've said
too much forgive me.

01:20:43.297 --> 01:20:46.133
But I do want you
to pray for Sam.

01:20:48.511 --> 01:20:51.180
And pray for me too that because

01:20:53.516 --> 01:20:57.996
the love that God has
shown me I can find ways

01:20:58.020 --> 01:21:00.523
to share that love with others.

01:21:02.066 --> 01:21:05.236
And I'll pray the
same for all of you.

01:21:08.990 --> 01:21:09.990
- Amen.

01:21:31.220 --> 01:21:32.555
- Yes thank you.

01:21:35.182 --> 01:21:36.725
Madison where's Roy?

01:21:36.726 --> 01:21:37.977
- I don't know.

01:21:39.604 --> 01:21:41.897
I told him you were
being discharged at 10.

01:21:43.649 --> 01:21:44.817
- That he did.

01:21:46.402 --> 01:21:49.697
Don't worry Sam he's probably
just stuck in traffic.

01:21:51.741 --> 01:21:52.825
- Good point.

01:21:54.452 --> 01:21:55.804
- My backpack.

01:21:55.828 --> 01:21:57.330
- Oh, here you go.

01:21:58.789 --> 01:22:00.434
Think I'm just gonna
call real quick.

01:22:00.458 --> 01:22:03.002
- Hi guys, it's a beautiful
day why don't we walk?

01:22:05.356 --> 01:22:06.356
I'll take over.

01:22:06.380 --> 01:22:08.049
- Take care now Sam.

01:22:10.426 --> 01:22:12.345
- Wherever the trail leads us.

01:22:13.346 --> 01:22:15.240
- Look Madison.

01:22:15.264 --> 01:22:17.326
Roy what's going on?

01:22:17.350 --> 01:22:19.036
- Let's find out.

